00022 static void 
00023 _factory_free(container_type *data, void *context)
00024 {
00025     if (data == NULL)
00026         return;
00027     
00028     if (data->name != NULL) {
00029         DEBUGMSGTL(("container", "  _factory_free_list() called for %s\n",
00030                     data->name));
00031         free((void *)data->name); /* SNMP_FREE wasted on object about to be freed */
00032     }
00033     free(data); /* SNMP_FREE wasted on param */
00034 }

00069 void
00070 netsnmp_container_free_list(void)
00071 {
00072     DEBUGMSGTL(("container", "netsnmp_container_free_list() called\n"));
00073     if (containers == NULL)
00074         return;
00075 
00076     /*
00077      * free memory used by each factory entry
00078      */
00079     CONTAINER_FOR_EACH(containers, _factory_free, NULL);
00080 
00081     /*
00082      * free factory container
00083      */
00084     CONTAINER_FREE(containers);
00085     containers = NULL;
00086 }

00088 int
00089 netsnmp_container_register(const char* name, netsnmp_factory *f)
00090 {
00091     container_type *ct, tmp;
00092 
00093     tmp.name = name;
00094     ct = CONTAINER_FIND(containers, &tmp);
00095     if (NULL!=ct) {
00096         DEBUGMSGT(("container_registry",
00097                    "replacing previous container factory\n"));
00098         ct->factory = f;
00099     }
00100     else {
00101         ct = SNMP_MALLOC_TYPEDEF(container_type);
00102         if (NULL == ct)
00103             return -1;
00104         ct->name = strdup(name);
00105         ct->factory = f;
00106         CONTAINER_INSERT(containers, ct);
00107     }
00108     DEBUGMSGT(("container_registry", "registered container factory %s (%s)\n",
00109                ct->name, f->product));
00110 
00111     return 0;
00112 }

00127 netsnmp_factory *
00128 netsnmp_container_find_factory(const char *type_list)
00129 {
00130     netsnmp_factory   *f = NULL;
00131     char              *list, *entry;
00132     char              *st;
00133 
00134     if (NULL==type_list)
00135         return NULL;
00136 
00137     list = strdup(type_list);
00138     entry = strtok_r(list, ":", &st);
00139     while(entry) {
00140         f = netsnmp_container_get_factory(entry);
00141         if (NULL != f)
00142             break;
00143         entry = strtok_r(NULL, ":", &st);
00144     }
00145 
00146     free(list);
00147     return f;
00148 }

00205 int CONTAINER_INSERT(netsnmp_container *x, const void *k)
00206 { 
00207     int rc2, rc = 0;
00208     
00210     while(x->prev)
00211         x = x->prev;
00212     while(x) {
00213         rc2 = x->insert(x,k);
00214         if (rc2) {
00215             snmp_log(LOG_ERR,"error on subcontainer insert (%d)\n", rc2);
00216             rc = rc2;
00217         }
00218         x = x->next;
00219     }
00220     return rc;
00221 }

00250 int CONTAINER_FREE(netsnmp_container *x)
00251 {
00252     int  rc2, rc = 0;
00253         
00255     while(x->next)
00256         x = x->next;
00257     while(x) {
00258         netsnmp_container *tmp;
00259         tmp = x->prev;
00260         if (NULL != x->container_name)
00261             SNMP_FREE(x->container_name);
00262         rc2 = x->cfree(x);
00263         if (rc2) {
00264             snmp_log(LOG_ERR,"error on subcontainer cfree (%d)\n", rc2);
00265             rc = rc2;
00266         }
00267         x = tmp;
00268     }
00269     return rc;
00270 }

00276 /*
00277  * clear all containers. When clearing the *first* container, and
00278  * *only* the first container, call the function f for each item.
00279  * After calling this function, all containers should be empty.
00280  */
00281 void CONTAINER_CLEAR(netsnmp_container *x, netsnmp_container_obj_func *f,
00282                     void *c)
00283 {
00285     while(x->next)
00286         x = x->next;
00287     while(x->prev) {
00288         x->clear(x, NULL, c);
00289         x = x->prev;
00290     }
00291     x->clear(x, f, c);
00292 }

00300  */
00301 netsnmp_container *SUBCONTAINER_FIND(netsnmp_container *x,
00302                                      const char* name)
00303 {
00304     if ((NULL == x) || (NULL == name))
00305         return NULL;
00306     
00308     while(x->prev)

00349 int
00350 netsnmp_compare_netsnmp_index(const void *lhs, const void *rhs)
00351 {
00352     int rc;
00353     netsnmp_assert((NULL != lhs) && (NULL != rhs));
00354     DEBUGIF("compare:index") {
00355         DEBUGMSGT(("compare:index", "compare "));
00356         DEBUGMSGSUBOID(("compare:index", ((const netsnmp_index *) lhs)->oids,
00357                      ((const netsnmp_index *) lhs)->len));
00358         DEBUGMSG(("compare:index", " to "));
00359         DEBUGMSGSUBOID(("compare:index", ((const netsnmp_index *) rhs)->oids,
00360                      ((const netsnmp_index *) rhs)->len));
00361         DEBUGMSG(("compare:index", "\n"));
00362     }
00363     rc = snmp_oid_compare(((const netsnmp_index *) lhs)->oids,
00364                           ((const netsnmp_index *) lhs)->len,
00365                           ((const netsnmp_index *) rhs)->oids,
00366                           ((const netsnmp_index *) rhs)->len);
00367     DEBUGMSGT(("compare:index", "result was %d\n", rc));
00368     return rc;
00369 }

00409 /*
00410  * compare two memory buffers
00411  *
00412  * since snmp strings aren't NULL terminated, we can't use strcmp. So
00413  * compare up to the length of the smaller, and then use length to
00414  * break any ties.
00415  */
00416 int
00417 netsnmp_compare_mem(const char * lhs, size_t lhs_len,
00418                     const char * rhs, size_t rhs_len)
00419 {
00420     int rc, min = SNMP_MIN(lhs_len, rhs_len);
00421 
00422     rc = memcmp(lhs, rhs, min);
00423     if((rc==0) && (lhs_len != rhs_len)) {
00424         if(lhs_len < rhs_len)
00425             rc = -1;
00426         else
00427             rc = 1;
00428     }
00429 
00430     return rc;
00431 }
